code-apex.title: Calculation for Apex Financial
code-apex.code:
import pandas as pd
from io import StringIO

csv_data = """First Name,Last Name,Company
Emma,Johnson,GreenScape Living
Liam,Smith,BlueSky Logistics
Olivia,Brown,QuantumLeap Tech
Noah,Davis,Horizon Media
Ava,Wilson,Nexus Retail
William,Martinez,BlueSky Logistics
Sophia,Anderson,GreenScape Living
James,Thomas,Gastronomy Inc.
Isabella,Jackson,Apex Financial
Benjamin,White,Innovate Dynamics
Mia,Harris,Summit Consulting
Lucas,Clark,Horizon Media
Amelia,Lewis,BlueSky Logistics
Mason,Robinson,BlueSky Logistics
Harper,Walker,Nexus Retail
Ethan,Hall,BlueSky Logistics
Evelyn,Allen,Summit Consulting
Alexander,Young,QuantumLeap Tech
Abigail,King,Innovate Dynamics
Michael,Wright,QuantumLeap Tech
"""

# Load the data
df = pd.read_csv(StringIO(csv_data))

# Filter data for "Apex Financial"
company_data = df[df['Company'] == 'Apex Financial']

# Count the number of users
total_users = len(company_data)

# Create a result for this company
result = pd.DataFrame({
    'Company': ['Apex Financial'],
    'Total Users': [total_users]
})

print(result)
